INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('229', '1', '2013-09-19 12:25:25', '2013-09-19 12:25:25', '<h1>Criminal Defense Attorney in Connecticut</h1>\r\n\r\nThousands of Americans are injured by defective products each year. These products can include toys, appliances, electrical wiring, power tools, loading and construction equipment, and flammable materials. There are three different types of product liability\r\n<ul class=\"yes-list\">\r\n   <li> Defectively manufactured products</li>\r\n    <li> Defectively designed products</li>\r\n    <li> Products with insufficient warnings or instructions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThere is no one law governing defective products in the U.S.; instead, product liability cases in Texas are considered in light of state negligence, breach of warranty, and strict liability laws. Any number of companies or individuals could be found guilty in a defective product suit, including the manufacturer, the person who constructed or installed the product, wholesale distributors, and retailers â anyone who helped to distribute the product and had sufficient reason to believe it was unsafe. Because of the complexity of product liability laws and the difficulty in proving exactly who was responsible, defective product cases require personal injury attorneys with years of experience in this legal sphere. At Powers Taylor, we have the experience necessary to aggressively defend your case.\r\n\r\nContact Powers Taylor to Get the Financial Compensation You Deserve\r\n\r\nDefective products can cause serious injuries that result in high medical bills, pain and suffering, and time off from work. When you have been injured because of manufacturer or retailer negligence, justice demands that you should not have to pay for your injuries. At Powers Taylor, we are committed to serving justice and to ensuring that you get full financial compensation for all losses you have sustained. Our Dallas-Fort Worth attorneys and litigators have an established reputation for dedication to their clients and aggressive legal counsel. If you have been injured by a defective product in Dallas, Arlington, Plano, or anywhere in Texas, contact us today to find out if you have a viable defective product claim and to get started on the path towards getting appropriate compensation. Call our Dallas office at 214-504-2121 or call toll free at 855-584-8787.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-19 12:25:25', '2013-09-19 12:25:25', '', '29', 'http://www.localhost.com/lawfirm/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('230', '1', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '<h1>Criminal Defense Attorney in Connecticut</h1>\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\nAttorney Jonathan R. Sills is a partner in the criminal defense law firm of TOMEO SILLS, LLC. and he has a statewide practice for representing clients in criminal and DUI matters. He handles criminal matters in every Geographical Area (G.A.) Court in Connecticut as well as the Judicial District (J.D.) Courts throughout the State.\r\n\r\nAttorney Sills was recently promoted to Senior partner by the firmâs founder, Steven A. Tomeo and together the two (2) partners author the Connecticut Practice Book Series book CONNECTICUT DUI LAW, which is published by West Publishing Company.\r\n\r\nAttorney Sills represents individuals at the Department of Motor Vehicles. The main office is located at 60 State Street, Wethersfield, CT 06161. DMV Hearings are also located at DMV offices located in Bridgeport, Old Saybrook and Waterbury. The firm has offices near each DMV location.\r\n\r\nAttorney Sills is no stranger to the Appellate Court process in the Connecticut Appellate Court in Hartford and the filing of Administrative Appeals to the Superior Court, New Britain Judicial District in New Britain.\r\n\r\nTHE FIRMâS TOLL FREE LINE IS 800-608-6636 FOR ALL OFFICES.\r\n\r\nThe convenience of each location enables the client to meet with the attorney at a location nearest the client. If you have a matter pending at one of the following courts, please call one of the above listed offices for a FREE CONSULTATION.\r\n\r\nThe Criminal Division hears cases where the state is prosecuting a person (the defendant) who is accused of breaking the law. The state is represented by a stateâs attorney. There are three kinds of criminal cases, depending on the severity of the offense: crimes which include felonies â punishable by prison sentences more than one year â and misdemeanors â punishable by prison sentences of one year or less; violations which include motor vehicle cases punishable by a fine only; and, infractions where a fine may be paid by mail without requiring a court appearance (for example, traffic tickets). All criminal cases but the most serious ones are heard in geographical area courts around the state.', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '2013-09-19 12:26:01', '', '29', 'http://www.localhost.com/lawfirm/29-revision-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
